cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.SY, cs.IT, cs.PF 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper deals with clock synchronization in wireless sensor networks. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is also likely as the proposed algorithm is fully distributed and asynchronous. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is relevant as the paper deals with clock skew and offset estimation, which are important in control systems. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is relevant as the paper mentions the Cram\'er-Rao bound, which is a fundamental limit in information theory. 
- cs.PF (Performance) is relevant as the paper discusses the convergence speed of the proposed algorithm.
